Before the mid-1990s, the substances of choice in the clubhouse were amphetamines and recreational drugs. The prevailing view was that top offensive performances in baseball demanded quick reflexes, good eye-hand coordination, quick feet, flexibility and strong wrists -- not bulky muscles. They would benefit from taking a step back and looking more carefully at the evolution of the steroid problem in baseball. Indeed, it was probably around 10 years ago that some people in baseball became aware that anabolic steroids were being used by some players. 